# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HassarPath | Scene: JaeidPath2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Weaving through the many busy streets and narrow alleys, he guided her towards his house."
    new "Weaving through the many busy streets and narrow alleys, he guided her towards his house."

    old "Perhaps in Rosanna, the house would have seemed decent enough, something fitting for a skilled tradesmen."
    new "Perhaps in Rosanna, the house would have seemed decent enough, something fitting for a skilled tradesmen."

    old "In this place, the house seemed nearer to a palace."
    new "In this place, the house seemed nearer to a palace."

    old "With most living in tents and very few even owning any settled structure, the house by contrast seemed more impressive."
    new "With most living in tents and very few even owning any settled structure, the house by contrast seemed more impressive."

    old "As soon as they stepped inside, the air instantly felt cooler to her skin."
    new "As soon as they stepped inside, the air instantly felt cooler to her skin."

    old "This is your house?"
    new "This is your house?"

    old "I have served the Khan for many years now, faithfully. Such service comes with its own rewards."
    new "I have served the Khan for many years now, faithfully. Such service comes with its own rewards."

    old "Sarah took in the house. There were decorations that seemed to hail from every corner of the world."
    new "Sarah took in the house. There were decorations that seemed to hail from every corner of the world."

    old "It gave the place an incoherent feeling. As if it was somewhat of a storage space, rather than a house that was lived in."
    new "It gave the place an incoherent feeling. As if it was somewhat of a storage space, rather than a house that was lived in."

    old "She looked at the serious and stoic face of Jaied. Perhaps that was exactly what his house was to him."
    new "She looked at the serious and stoic face of Jaied. Perhaps that was exactly what his house was to him."

    old "It's...nice."
    new "It's...nice."

    old "In some way she meant it."
    new "In some way she meant it."

    old "Jaeid shrugged."
    new "Jaeid shrugged."

    old "This house resides in what is known as the Old Quarter."
    new "This house resides in what is known as the Old Quarter."

    old "Al'Gahaem is a city that rises and falls in cycles."
    new "Al'Gahaem is a city that rises and falls in cycles."

    old "He faced her."
    new "He faced her."

    old "Al'Gahaem is centrally located in the desert. It resides on one of the few large rock formations that allow any real construction."
    new "Al'Gahaem is centrally located in the desert. It resides on one of the few large rock formations that allow any real construction."

    old "As a result, it is one of the very few places in the desert that allows for a city to exist at all."
    new "As a result, it is one of the very few places in the desert that allows for a city to exist at all."

    old "Additionally, it sits upon a large vein of coal, allowing a degree of industry needed for the production of weaponry. Siege engines and such."
    new "Additionally, it sits upon a large vein of coal, allowing a degree of industry needed for the production of weaponry. Siege engines and such."

    old "Sarah listened intently."
    new "Sarah listened intently."

    old "The desert sat next to Rosanna, but she had never heard or considered any of this."
    new "The desert sat next to Rosanna, but she had never heard or considered any of this."

    old "The problem that Al'Gahaem faces is that it is too important and too centrally located."
    new "The problem that Al'Gahaem faces is that it is too important and too centrally located."

    old "This means that no single tribe can hope to hold it, because all the other tribes would prevent it."
    new "This means that no single tribe can hope to hold it, because all the other tribes would prevent it."

    old "And so in most ages, the city slowly withers and dies."
    new "And so in most ages, the city slowly withers and dies."

    old "The soldiers leave with their money. The merchants quickly follow. The craftsmen depart after."
    new "The soldiers leave with their money. The merchants quickly follow. The craftsmen depart after."

    old "Then the city shrinks all the way down to the Old Quarter, the small section of the city that is permanent."
    new "Then the city shrinks all the way down to the Old Quarter, the small section of the city that is permanent."

    old "Sarah nodded. She had only ever imagined cities to be permanent, like the capital back in Rosanna."
    new "Sarah nodded. She had only ever imagined cities to be permanent, like the capital back in Rosanna."

    old "Though she now realized, that was likely not permanent either, after the fall."
    new "Though she now realized, that was likely not permanent either, after the fall."

    old "However, whenever the Tribes are united under the hand of a single Khan, these disputes are set aside."
    new "However, whenever the Tribes are united under the hand of a single Khan, these disputes are set aside."

    old "The Khan settles in the city and the tribes put to rest their disagreements. For a time."
    new "The Khan settles in the city and the tribes put to rest their disagreements. For a time."

    old "Then they flood into the city."
    new "Then they flood into the city."

    old "The soldiers bring their loot. The merchants eagerly flood in to chase after the wages of the soldiers. And the craftsmen follow."
    new "The soldiers bring their loot. The merchants eagerly flood in to chase after the wages of the soldiers. And the craftsmen follow."

    old "So the city dies, and so it is reborn. Cycle after cycle."
    new "So the city dies, and so it is reborn. Cycle after cycle."

    old "So long as there is a Khan, the city breathes."
    new "So long as there is a Khan, the city breathes."

    old "Sarah looked deep into his eyes."
    new "Sarah looked deep into his eyes."

    old "And when the Khan dies?"
    new "And when the Khan dies?"

    old "He smiled, a pained smile."
    new "He smiled, a pained smile."

    old "Then this city will fade back into the desert, mostly. To await the return of another Khan."
    new "Then this city will fade back into the desert, mostly. To await the return of another Khan."

    old "Doesn't that worry you? That all this might...fade?"
    new "Doesn't that worry you? That all this might...fade?"

    old "No, not this time. Khan Hassar...he will be different from the others."
    new "No, not this time. Khan Hassar...he will be different from the others."

    old "The Khan's of the past were men of great power and great ambition. But what drove them was small."
    new "The Khan's of the past were men of great power and great ambition. But what drove them was small."

    old "Wealth. Women. Land."
    new "Wealth. Women. Land."

    old "Their hordes grew fat and collapsed into infighting."
    new "Their hordes grew fat and collapsed into infighting."

    old "Khan Hassar...he is a great warrior in his own right, but more than that, he is moved by something greater than greed."
    new "Khan Hassar...he is a great warrior in his own right, but more than that, he is moved by something greater than greed."

    old "He will set the world right."
    new "He will set the world right."

    old "Sarah felt her heart sink as she listened to Jaeid speak."
    new "Sarah felt her heart sink as she listened to Jaeid speak."

    old "What she had seen of him so far made her believe he was a good man, or perhaps at the very least a decent one."
    new "What she had seen of him so far made her believe he was a good man, or perhaps at the very least a decent one."

    old "She found it hard to reconcile that image of him with the man who so clearly supported his Khan. The man that had ruined her country. Made her a slave."
    new "She found it hard to reconcile that image of him with the man who so clearly supported his Khan. The man that had ruined her country. Made her a slave."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard movement coming down the hall."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard movement coming down the hall."

    old "Why on earth are you making such a wicked racket?"
    new "Why on earth are you making such a wicked racket?"

    old "I swear, you're home not for a minute and I'm already stressed!"
    new "I swear, you're home not for a minute and I'm already stressed!"

    old "Sarah turned towards the voice and saw a woman turn around the corner."
    new "Sarah turned towards the voice and saw a woman turn around the corner."

    old "The woman suddenly stopped herself, caught in surprise."
    new "The woman suddenly stopped herself, caught in surprise."

    old "Her eyes went from Jaeid, to Sarah, and back again."
    new "Her eyes went from Jaeid, to Sarah, and back again."

    old "Sarah saw Jaied step forward."
    new "Sarah saw Jaied step forward."

    old "This, as you so kindly called her, is Sarah."
    new "This, as you so kindly called her, is Sarah."

    old "Ooh Jaied..."
    new "Ooh Jaied..."

    old "I mean, the brothels I can understand, but do you really have to bring them home?"
    new "I mean, the brothels I can understand, but do you really have to bring them home?"

    old "Sarah saw Jaied become flustered."
    new "Sarah saw Jaied become flustered."

    old "No! That's not what this is at all!"
    new "No! That's not what this is at all!"

    old "Well it is your house, so your rules I suppose."
    new "Well it is your house, so your rules I suppose."

    old "But can you stuff a rag in her mouth when you fuck her? I'm trying to work."
    new "But can you stuff a rag in her mouth when you fuck her? I'm trying to work."

    old "Jasmine!"
    new "Jasmine!"

    old "Apologize at once! She is not some brothel whore!"
    new "Apologize at once! She is not some brothel whore!"

    old "Sarah could see confusion the woman's face, the woman Jaeid had called Jasmine."
    new "Sarah could see confusion the woman's face, the woman Jaeid had called Jasmine."

    old "Sarah stepped forward and extended her own hand."
    new "Sarah stepped forward and extended her own hand."

    old "Sarah Rose, nice to meet you."
    new "Sarah Rose, nice to meet you."

    old "The woman took her hand, shaking it with an expression of confusion on her face."
    new "The woman took her hand, shaking it with an expression of confusion on her face."

    old "Sarah Rose..."
    new "Sarah Rose..."

    old "Her eyes went wide."
    new "Her eyes went wide."

    old "Sarah! The princess? Really?"
    new "Sarah! The princess? Really?"

    old "Didn't Hassar task you to bring her to him directly? What is she doing here?"
    new "Didn't Hassar task you to bring her to him directly? What is she doing here?"

    old "I already brought her before the Khan...but she was not what he expected..."
    new "I already brought her before the Khan...but she was not what he expected..."

    old "Sarah saw Jasmine looking back at her, eyes still wide."
    new "Sarah saw Jasmine looking back at her, eyes still wide."

    old "I never met a real princess before."
    new "I never met a real princess before."

    old "Sarah watched as the woman's eyes ran up and down her body. She suddenly felt exposed again."
    new "Sarah watched as the woman's eyes ran up and down her body. She suddenly felt exposed again."

    old "Sarah wrapped her arms, covering her breasts."
    new "Sarah wrapped her arms, covering her breasts."

    old "Well...I'm not a princess. Not anymore, anyway."
    new "Well...I'm not a princess. Not anymore, anyway."

    old "Jasmine chuckled."
    new "Jasmine chuckled."

    old "Yeah, I guess that's true."
    new "Yeah, I guess that's true."

    old "Sorry, that's not...I didn't mean to come off as rude or..."
    new "Sorry, that's not...I didn't mean to come off as rude or..."

    old "Jasmine sighed."
    new "Jasmine sighed."

    old "I can be odd. I don't mean anything by it, I just am. You can ask him."
    new "I can be odd. I don't mean anything by it, I just am. You can ask him."

    old "She gestured at Jaeid."
    new "She gestured at Jaeid."

    old "Anyway, I'm sorry if said anything to make you upset."
    new "Anyway, I'm sorry if said anything to make you upset."

    old "Happy? Good enough of an apology?"
    new "Happy? Good enough of an apology?"

    old "Jaied sternly nodded."
    new "Jaied sternly nodded."

    old "As good as one we can hope to expect from you, I suppose."
    new "As good as one we can hope to expect from you, I suppose."

    old "Jaied turned to Sarah."
    new "Jaied turned to Sarah."

    old "I should have perhaps prepared you, but this here is Jasmine."
    new "I should have perhaps prepared you, but this here is Jasmine."

    old "Sarah saw the woman looking at her, a blank expression on her face, not close to any emotion."
    new "Sarah saw the woman looking at her, a blank expression on her face, not close to any emotion."

    old "Jasmine has lived with me for...Gods, years now I imagine."
    new "Jasmine has lived with me for...Gods, years now I imagine."

    old "Is she your..."
    new "Is she your..."

    old "Sarah didn't finish the sentence, but the words were spoken still. Partner. Wife."
    new "Sarah didn't finish the sentence, but the words were spoken still. Partner. Wife."

    old "Jasmine suddenly laughed."
    new "Jasmine suddenly laughed."

    old "The Gods couldn't save him if he tried anything with me."
    new "The Gods couldn't save him if he tried anything with me."

    old "No, I'm a cartographer."
    new "No, I'm a cartographer."

    old "I grew up in the same province as Jaeid. Captured in the same raid."
    new "I grew up in the same province as Jaeid. Captured in the same raid."

    old "What Jaeid can do with languages, I can do with maps. Together we make a half-decent team."
    new "What Jaeid can do with languages, I can do with maps. Together we make a half-decent team."

    old "We're part of the commission that works on formulating the Tribal relationships with foreign powers."
    new "We're part of the commission that works on formulating the Tribal relationships with foreign powers."

    old "Foreign powers? I...thought the Tribes just raided. Conquered."
    new "Foreign powers? I...thought the Tribes just raided. Conquered."

    old "Jasmine nodded."
    new "Jasmine nodded."

    old "Ooh, they do. But the desert is a large place and it connects to many different nations. Both on your side and the Far-East."
    new "Ooh, they do. But the desert is a large place and it connects to many different nations. Both on your side and the Far-East."

    old "Going to war with everyone is a good recipe to lose."
    new "Going to war with everyone is a good recipe to lose."

    old "So we, along with many others, plot out ways for the Tribes to remain on good terms."
    new "So we, along with many others, plot out ways for the Tribes to remain on good terms."

    old "How do you do that?"
    new "How do you do that?"

    old "Mostly we send emmisaries to demand tributes. Spares the Tribes the effort of a war, still brings in some loot."
    new "Mostly we send emmisaries to demand tributes. Spares the Tribes the effort of a war, still brings in some loot."

    old "It's efficient, but the Tribesmen don't much care for such nuances."
    new "It's efficient, but the Tribesmen don't much care for such nuances."

    old "Sarah leaned in, listening intently."
    new "Sarah leaned in, listening intently."

    old "Theirs is a martial culture. They are men of war, both factually and spiritually."
    new "Theirs is a martial culture. They are men of war, both factually and spiritually."

    old "They consider loot earned without bloodshed to be...dishonorable."
    new "They consider loot earned without bloodshed to be...dishonorable."

    old "They believe that they are entitled to the women they conquer, because they are the strongest."
    new "They believe that they are entitled to the women they conquer, because they are the strongest."

    old "If a woman is just given or goes freely...well it clashes with how they view the world."
    new "If a woman is just given or goes freely...well it clashes with how they view the world."

    old "Then why do they allow you to contact these places at all?"
    new "Then why do they allow you to contact these places at all?"

    old "Jasmine smiled."
    new "Jasmine smiled."

    old "Because the Khan is more practical than most of his kind."
    new "Because the Khan is more practical than most of his kind."

    old "He understands the value of a smart strategy. And the wealth it brings in mostly flows to his coffers first."
    new "He understands the value of a smart strategy. And the wealth it brings in mostly flows to his coffers first."

    old "Enough, Jasmine. No need to bore our guest with your tales."
    new "Enough, Jasmine. No need to bore our guest with your tales."

    old "Jasmine frowned."
    new "Jasmine frowned."

    old "I don't think she's bored."
    new "I don't think she's bored."

    old "Regardless, the sun is already setting. She is in a new and unfamiliar place. Let her find her orientation first."
    new "Regardless, the sun is already setting. She is in a new and unfamiliar place. Let her find her orientation first."

    old "Jasmine shrugged."
    new "Jasmine shrugged."

    old "Fine. Sorry if I bothered you, Sarah."
    new "Fine. Sorry if I bothered you, Sarah."

    old "You didn't, not at all. It's interesting to learn more about this place."
    new "You didn't, not at all. It's interesting to learn more about this place."

    old "Not only was it interesting. It also made her understand how the Tribes worked."
    new "Not only was it interesting. It also made her understand how the Tribes worked."

    old "Understanding that would be critical if she ever wanted to find a way to escape."
    new "Understanding that would be critical if she ever wanted to find a way to escape."

    old "Jaeid looked around the room for a moment."
    new "Jaeid looked around the room for a moment."

    old "I don't think we..."
    new "I don't think we..."

    old "Jaeid looked at Jasmine."
    new "Jaeid looked at Jasmine."

    old "Do you think she could-"
    new "Do you think she could-"

    old "Jasmine threw up her hand."
    new "Jasmine threw up her hand."

    old "You better not try and steal my workroom!"
    new "You better not try and steal my workroom!"

    old "Jaied sighed."
    new "Jaied sighed."

    old "Well where then?"
    new "Well where then?"

    old "Jasmine gestured at a couch near the other side of the room."
    new "Jasmine gestured at a couch near the other side of the room."

    old "Just get her some blankets and she can sleep on the couch."
    new "Just get her some blankets and she can sleep on the couch."

    old "We can go ahead and clear out one of the spare rooms tomorrow and she can have that."
    new "We can go ahead and clear out one of the spare rooms tomorrow and she can have that."

    old "Or hell, she can clear it out for us. If we're going to be having a slave over anyway."
    new "Or hell, she can clear it out for us. If we're going to be having a slave over anyway."

    old "Jaeid took a step forward."
    new "Jaeid took a step forward."

    old "Don't call her that."
    new "Don't call her that."

    old "She will be here under our roof as a guest, not a slave or a servant. Not mine and not yours."
    new "She will be here under our roof as a guest, not a slave or a servant. Not mine and not yours."

    old "Am I clear?"
    new "Am I clear?"

    old "Sarah witnessed the moment suddenly grow tense."
    new "Sarah witnessed the moment suddenly grow tense."

    old "A pause lingered. Then, Jasmine spoke."
    new "A pause lingered. Then, Jasmine spoke."

    old "Sure, whatever. I was just joking. I'll make sure to get her some blankets."
    new "Sure, whatever. I was just joking. I'll make sure to get her some blankets."

    old "As the night set in, Jasmine delivered the promised blankets and Sarah settled in on the couch."
    new "As the night set in, Jasmine delivered the promised blankets and Sarah settled in on the couch."

    old "Jasmine for her part dissapeared back into her own study, and Sarah didn't see much of her for the rest of the day."
    new "Jasmine for her part dissapeared back into her own study, and Sarah didn't see much of her for the rest of the day."

    old "By now, only faint moonlight slipped in through one of the windows."
    new "By now, only faint moonlight slipped in through one of the windows."

    old "Jaeid was still standing in the room."
    new "Jaeid was still standing in the room."

    old "Do you think you will be alright?"
    new "Do you think you will be alright?"

    old "Sarah looked around and nodded."
    new "Sarah looked around and nodded."

    old "This was far from what she was used to, but given her circumstances, more than she had expected."
    new "This was far from what she was used to, but given her circumstances, more than she had expected."

    old "Thank you for the blankets."
    new "Thank you for the blankets."

    old "And thank you for what you did for me today...if you hadn't..."
    new "And thank you for what you did for me today...if you hadn't..."

    old "Jaied waved his hands, dismissing her concern."
    new "Jaied waved his hands, dismissing her concern."

    old "Do not think you owe me any thanks, Sarah. I was able to help you, and so I did. If I had not done so...I would not have been able to live with myself."
    new "Do not think you owe me any thanks, Sarah. I was able to help you, and so I did. If I had not done so...I would not have been able to live with myself."

    old "You're very kind to me, Jaied."
    new "You're very kind to me, Jaied."

    old "She saw him smile, breaking through his otherwise stoic face."
    new "She saw him smile, breaking through his otherwise stoic face."

    old "Take care for the night, Sarah Rose."
    new "Take care for the night, Sarah Rose."

    old "Tomorrow we will see to getting you a proper room."
    new "Tomorrow we will see to getting you a proper room."

    old "Sarah watched as Jaied left the room, retiring to his own."
    new "Sarah watched as Jaied left the room, retiring to his own."

    old "When the door fell shut, the room was suddenly quiet."
    new "When the door fell shut, the room was suddenly quiet."

    old "Sarah sat alone in the dark, faintly lit moonlight."
    new "Sarah sat alone in the dark, faintly lit moonlight."

    old "Though the house was silent, it was the kind that pounded on one's ears like a hammer."
    new "Though the house was silent, it was the kind that pounded on one's ears like a hammer."

    old "Sarah laid down and pulled the covers close."
    new "Sarah laid down and pulled the covers close."

    old "It had been the first time all day that she had some modicum of modesty."
    new "It had been the first time all day that she had some modicum of modesty."

    old "It made her feel safe in this otherwise strange place."
    new "It made her feel safe in this otherwise strange place."

